    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in MCE_send_M2_SETUP_RESPONSE due to missing mutex lock\n\n### Summary\nThe MCE_send_M2_SETUP_RESPONSE function in the M2AP interface management was accessing the global shared variable m2ap_mce_data_from_enb->assoc_id without proper mutex protection, leading to potential race conditions when multiple threads accessed this data concurrently. This could result in incorrect association IDs being used for SCTP data transmission, causing message delivery failures or crashes under high load conditions.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident during M2 setup procedures when multiple eNBs were connecting simultaneously to the MCE.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE.c`: Added mutex to protect access to m2ap_mce_data_from_enb global variable\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_common.h`: Added function declarations for mutex lock/unlock functions\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_MCE_interface_management.c`: Protected all critical sections accessing m2ap_mce_data_from_enb->assoc_id with mutex locks\n\n"
}